{"name":"Chases","content":"<h1>Creating a new chase</h1>\n<p>To create a chase create a new item of type chase.</p>\n<p>Only the keeper should have access to that item.</p>\n<p>A chase is composed of a succession of locations. Each location can be separated by an obstacle (barrier or hazard).</p>\n<p>A hazard will always be crossed but failing the check will slow you down.</p>\n<p>A barrier will stop you until you successfully pass or destroy it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_chase.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"273\" /></p>\n<p>The chase sheet os divided in 3 parts.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A header where you will see information about current location once a chase is started.</li>\n<li>A chase setup tab. This will allows you to create and follow the chase.</li>\n<li>A participant list wher you can setup your participant. This tab will not work after the chase started.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Adding a participant.</h1>\n<p>To add a participant click on the plus sign on the particpant list or drag an actor or a token.</p>\n<p>Note that it is not mandatory to have a actor associated with a particpant. This will allows for fast setup or to add someone on the fly to the chase.</p>\n<p>To be able to add a token to the chase a few control have benn added to character and NPC sheets :</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_controls.jpg\" width=\"169\" height=\"136\" /></p>\n<p>Those icons will give additional informations.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Indicate that this actor is a synthetic actor (instance of an actor)</li>\n<li>Indicate that actor's data are not linked. Each instance of that actor has his own properties.</li>\n<li>Indicate that this actor has an associated token. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">You can drag and drop this onto a chase location or on the participant list</span></strong>.</li>\n<li>Indicate that actor's data are linked to an actor in the actors directory.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Draging a token to the participant list or to a location will activate the importer window.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_participant.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can setup your participant. All fields can be changed. Note that you can select a different initiative and speed check. This is non standard in the CoC, but allows to setup unusual chases (futuristic matrice chase, dreamlands chase...)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Clicking this will change the participant side from prey to chaser.</li>\n<li>Clicking this will trigger a speed check. Note that there will be no player entries necessary nor any roll card displayed.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Particpant list</h1>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/participant_list.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"256\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can have the list of particpant to the chase.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Will trigger a chase roll. This will create a roll card if the particpant has an associated actor (it's not a dummy). Holding shift will fast forward and solve the card.</li>\n<li>This will clear the speed roll if any, or delete the particpant.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/participant_list_2.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"226\" /></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Roll card waiting to get resolved in the chat.</li>\n<li>Speed check rolled. You can click this to get the details.</li>\n<li>To reset the speed check.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/roll_card.jpg\" width=\"288\" height=\"134\" /></p>\n<h1>Chase setup</h1>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/chase_init.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"227\" /></p>\n<p>To setup a chase enter the initial numbers of locations and click initialize.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/chase_initialized.png\" width=\"454\" height=\"227\" /></p>\n<p>The chase is initialized, you can adjust some options.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>This is the chase track, the location in white are initials locations. The location in grey are actual chase locations.</li>\n<li>Selecting this will include in the chase participants who would have otherwise been able to escape. </li>\n<li>Selecting this will include in the chase participants who would have been excluded for being too slow.</li>\n<li>This is the number of laction between the slowest prey and the fastest chaser.</li>\n<li>This is the strating location of the fastest prey. Setting this to 0 will place him just before the start. 1 will place him at the start. -1 will place him 1 location before the start.</li>\n<li>This will animate token when they move to a new location.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Cut to the chase.</h1>\n<p>When you are ready you can cut to the chase. If not all participant have a speed check this will trigger a warning and will not let you start.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"fiK9kI7E1ThE0aAT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.iUQwB5WExK6sq9in"}},"_id":"POxSHclKlwaHTQqU"}
{"_id":"POxSHclKlwaHTQqU","name":"Chases","content":"<h1>Creating a new chase</h1>\n<p>To create a chase create a new item of type chase.</p>\n<p>Only the keeper should have access to that item.</p>\n<p>A chase is composed of a succession of locations. Each location can be separated by an obstacle (barrier or hazard).</p>\n<p>A hazard will always be crossed but failing the check will slow you down.</p>\n<p>A barrier will stop you until you successfully pass or destroy it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_chase.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"273\" /></p>\n<p>The chase sheet os divided in 3 parts.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A header where you will see information about current location once a chase is started.</li>\n<li>A chase setup tab. This will allows you to create and follow the chase.</li>\n<li>A participant list wher you can setup your participant. This tab will not work after the chase started.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Adding a participant.</h1>\n<p>To add a participant click on the plus sign on the particpant list or drag an actor or a token.</p>\n<p>Note that it is not mandatory to have a actor associated with a particpant. This will allows for fast setup or to add someone on the fly to the chase.</p>\n<p>To be able to add a token to the chase a few control have benn added to character and NPC sheets :</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_controls.jpg\" width=\"169\" height=\"136\" /></p>\n<p>Those icons will give additional informations.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Indicate that this actor is a synthetic actor (instance of an actor)</li>\n<li>Indicate that actor's data are not linked. Each instance of that actor has his own properties.</li>\n<li>Indicate that this actor has an associated token. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">You can drag and drop this onto a chase location or on the participant list</span></strong>.</li>\n<li>Indicate that actor's data are linked to an actor in the actors directory.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Draging a token to the participant list or to a location will activate the importer window.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/new_participant.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can setup your participant. All fields can be changed. Note that you can select a different initiative and speed check. This is non standard in the CoC, but allows to setup unusual chases (futuristic matrice chase, dreamlands chase...)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Clicking this will change the participant side from prey to chaser.</li>\n<li>Clicking this will trigger a speed check. Note that there will be no player entries necessary nor any roll card displayed.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Particpant list</h1>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/participant_list.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"256\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can have the list of particpant to the chase.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Will trigger a chase roll. This will create a roll card if the particpant has an associated actor (it's not a dummy). Holding shift will fast forward and solve the card.</li>\n<li>This will clear the speed roll if any, or delete the particpant.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/participant_list_2.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"226\" /></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Roll card waiting to get resolved in the chat.</li>\n<li>Speed check rolled. You can click this to get the details.</li>\n<li>To reset the speed check.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/roll_card.jpg\" width=\"288\" height=\"134\" /></p>\n<h1>Chase setup</h1>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/chase_init.jpg\" width=\"454\" height=\"227\" /></p>\n<p>To setup a chase enter the initial numbers of locations and click initialize.</p>\n<p><img src=\"systems/CoC7/assets/manual/chases/chase_initialized.png\" width=\"454\" height=\"227\" /></p>\n<p>The chase is initialized, you can adjust some options.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>This is the chase track, the location in white are initials locations. The location in grey are actual chase locations.</li>\n<li>Selecting this will include in the chase participants who would have otherwise been able to escape. </li>\n<li>Selecting this will include in the chase participants who would have been excluded for being too slow.</li>\n<li>This is the number of laction between the slowest prey and the fastest chaser.</li>\n<li>This is the strating location of the fastest prey. Setting this to 0 will place him just before the start. 1 will place him at the start. -1 will place him 1 location before the start.</li>\n<li>This will animate token when they move to a new location.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Cut to the chase.</h1>\n<p>When you are ready you can cut to the chase. If not all participant have a speed check this will trigger a warning and will not let you start.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>ddd</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"fiK9kI7E1ThE0aAT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.iUQwB5WExK6sq9in"}}}
